data.description: Welcome to 426 E Byrd BLVD in Universal City-a property that exudes both charm and practicality. Boasting a range of notable features, this residence presents an enticing opportunity for discerning buyers and savvy investors alike.    Let's start with sustainability. Equipped with solar panels and surrounded by mature trees, this home not only offers eco-friendly energy solutions but also creates a serene environment that enhances the overall living experience.    Parking and storage are a breeze with the oversized garage and additional parking space. Furthermore, the inclusion of a washer and dryer adds a layer of convenience to daily life.    Enhanced energy efficiency is ensured by the installation of new doors and windows, contributing to reduced utility costs and increased comfort throughout the year.    Location-wise, the property's proximity to Randolph AFB positions it as an attractive option for rental investment, appealing to military personnel. Moreover, the absence of an HOA provides residents with a greater degree of flexibility and autonomy.    Adding to its appeal, the roof is just a couple years old, providing peace of mind and potentially reducing maintenance costs for the new owner.    Whether you're seeking a comfortable residence or a lucrative rental opportunity, this property ticks all the boxes. Schedule a viewing today to experience its full potential firsthand.
